NAME
    DateTime::Duration::Lite - Duration objects for date math (lite version)

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of DateTime::Duration::Lite (from
    Perl distribution DateTime-Duration-Lite), released on 2017-10-18.

SYNOPSIS
    Use like you would DateTime::Duration.

DESCRIPTION
    EXPERIMENTAL, EARLY RELEASE.

    This class is an alternative to DateTime::Duration. The goal is to
    provide a reasonably compatible interface with less {startup overhead,
    code, memory usage}.

HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/DateTime-Duration-Lite>.

SOURCE
    Source repository is at
    <https://github.com/perlancar/perl-DateTime-Duration-Lite>.

BUGS
    Please report any bugs or feature requests on the bugtracker website
    <https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Name=DateTime-Duration-Lit
    e>

    When submitting a bug or request, please include a test-file or a patch
    to an existing test-file that illustrates the bug or desired feature.

